cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance of NOMA and OMA in the context of 5G networks and Machine Type Communications (MTC), which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the concept of Age of Information (AoI), which is a measure of the freshness of information in a communication system. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper leverages the notion of Stochastic Hybrid Systems (SHS) to analyze the performance of NOMA and OMA. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper provides a comparison between NOMA and OMA in terms of average AoI, which can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the potential of NOMA and OMA in the context of 5G networks, which are expected to support multimedia applications.
